# Automaton Auditor — Agent Rules

## Project Description

This project is a **Chroma Color Mixing and Inventory SaaS platform** built with **FastAPI**, following a **multi-tenant architecture**. The system allows salons to:

- Track color formulas used on customers
- Track inventory of color products in grams/mL
- Calculate cost per service
- Maintain customer history
- Support multiple salon tenants

---

## Specifications / SRS

### Project Overview

- Multi-tenant SaaS for salons
- Users: Stylists, Managers, Salon Owners
- Tracks inventory by grams/mL (not whole tubes)
- Maintains detailed audit logs for inventory transactions
- Formula tracking with cost calculation

### User Stories

#### Salon Owner
- Manage salon locations
- Add/manage employees
- Track inventory levels and costs
- See products needing restocking

#### Stylist / Employee
- Log in
- Select customer
- Record formula
- Auto-update inventory

#### Salon Manager
- Monitor inventory levels
- Track usage and waste
- Track service costs

#### SaaS Platform Owner
- Multi-tenant support
- Data separation per salon
- Scalable to thousands of salons

### System Architecture

- **Tenant** → **Location** → **Users** → **Customers**
- **Product Catalog** → **Tenant Products** → **Inventory Items**
- **Formulas** → **Formula Items** → **Inventory Transactions**
- Stack: Python 3.11+, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Pydantic, LangChain, LangGraph

### Tables / Entities (Abbreviated)

- tenants (id, name, plan, status, created_at)
- locations (id, tenant_id, name, address, timezone)
- users (id, tenant_id, default_location_id, full_name, email, role)
- customers (id, tenant_id, home_location_id, full_name, phone, email)
- brands, product_lines, products
- tenant_products (tenant_id, product_id, custom_name, is_enabled, tracking_unit, default_unit_cost)
- inventory_items (tenant_id, location_id, tenant_product_id, on_hand_qty, reorder_level_qty)
- formulas, formula_items, inventory_txns

### Inventory Tracking

- Track in grams or milliliters for precise cost
- Deduct inventory automatically when formulas are used
- Audit all transactions in `inventory_txns`

