## Specs: Where to Look and When

All authoritative specs live in **`SRS documentation/`**. Follow them for requirements, architecture, contracts, and conventions.

| File | What it does | When to check |
|------|----------------|---------------|
| **`SRS documentation/index.qmd`** | Complete system requirements specification (SRS). Source of truth for *what* the system must do, entity relationships, table schemas, user stories, and business logic. | Before designing or implementing any feature; when in doubt about a requirement; when defining models, schemas, or API contracts. |
| **`.cursor/rules/agent.mdc`** | Technical standards, architectural style, tech stack (FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Pydantic), API patterns, file layout (`src/models/`, `src/schemas/`, `src/crud/`, `src/routers/`), multi-tenant isolation rules. | When choosing technologies, patterns, or file locations; when writing new modules; when ensuring multi-tenant data isolation. |
| **`src/models/*.py`** | SQLAlchemy ORM models defining database schema, relationships, constraints, and foreign keys. Reference for table structure and entity relationships. | When implementing CRUD operations; when adding new entities; when verifying foreign key relationships and constraints. |
| **`src/schemas/*.py`** | Pydantic v2 schemas for API request/response validation. Defines `Base`, `Create`, `Update`, and `Read` schemas per entity. | When implementing API endpoints; when validating input/output; when defining API contracts. |
| **`src/crud/*.py`** | CRUD operations with multi-tenant filtering. All queries must filter by `tenant_id` for data isolation. | When implementing business logic; when adding new operations; when ensuring tenant isolation. |
| **`src/routers/*.py`** | FastAPI route handlers. RESTful endpoints organized by resource (tenants, users, customers, products, inventory, formulas). | When adding new endpoints; when implementing authentication/authorization; when documenting API behavior. |

